Class Contributor

java.lang.Object
io.github.thebusybiscuit.slimefun4.core.services.github.Contributor
public class Contributor extends Object
Represents a Contributor who contributed to a GitHub repository.

      @Nonnull public List<Map.Entry<String,Integer>> getContributions()
      This returns a List of contributions for this Contributor. Each entry consists of a String (for the role) and an Integer (for the amount of commits).
      Returns:
      A List of contributions for this Contributor

    • getContributions

      Parameters:
      role - The role for which to count the contributions.
      Returns:
      The amount of contributions this Contributor submitted as the given role

    • getTexture

      @Nonnull public String getTexture()
      Returns this contributor's head texture. If no texture could be found, or it hasn't been pulled yet, then it will return a placeholder texture.
      Returns:
      A Base64-Head Texture

    • getTexture

      @Nonnull protected String getTexture(@Nonnull GitHubService github)
      Returns this contributor's head texture. If no texture could be found, or it hasn't been pulled yet, then it will return a placeholder texture.
      Parameters:
      github - Our GitHubService instance
      Returns:
      A Base64-Head Texture

    • hasTexture

      public boolean hasTexture()
      This method will return whether this instance of Contributor has pulled a texture yet.

      This sets the skin texture of this Contributor or clears it.

    • getTotalContributions

      public int getTotalContributions()
      This returns the total amount of contributions towards this project for this Contributor.
      Returns:
      The total amount of contributions

    • getDisplayName

      @Nonnull public String getDisplayName()
      This returns the final display name for this Contributor. The display name is basically the GitHub username but if the Minecraft username differs, it will be appended in brackets behind the GitHub username.
      Returns:
      The final display name of this Contributor.

    • getPosition

      public int getPosition()
      This returns the position on where to order this Contributor. This is just a convenience method for a Comparator, it is equivalent to getTotalContributions() multiplied by minus one.
      Returns:
      The position of this Contributor in terms for positioning and ordering.
